trend_summary: From earliest to latest scenes the corridor evolves from a leafy edge-city to a more consolidated suburb. Industrial estates intensify along the highway, new cloverleaf and service roads appear, and housing pockets fill vacant lots. Tree cover slightly declines but parks and a sports field offset some loss.
notable_changes: Large white-roof warehouses added south of the central highway after the second image.
Cloverleaf interchange built at the southwest corner, replacing simpler junction.
Residential infill in northern neighbourhoods reduces scattered woodland gaps.
Open field redeveloped into a rectangular sports complex by mid-series.
Riparian and roadside vegetation management increases overall greening despite infill.
